page.title: 01GENERAL DESCRIPTION OF BLOCK
page.content:
05600165 FROM O/S MAP TQ66/77 The Meopham block is on the periphery of the London green belt on the dip slope of the North Downs between New Ash Green 610 653 and Meopham 640 653. The landscape lies at a general altitude of 500feet above sea level and is one of rolling countryside and deciduous woodland indented with dry valleys running South to North.The land use is primaily grazing for cattle,sheep and hoses with some land given to supporting arable crops and market gardening.The underlying rocks are chalk and clay with flint.
